FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE, BOVINE - KAZAKHSTAN
*******************************************
A ProMED post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
1998
-------
Foot & mouth disease - Kazakhstan 981025144534
Date: Fri, 01 Oct 1999 15:06:04 -0500
From: "Tam Garland" <TGARLAND@cvm.tamu.edu>
Source: OIE Reporting 24 Sep 1999

See also: 11 December 1998, 23 October 1998
Emergency report
Translation of a communication received on 20 September 1999 from Dr Sh. Zh.
Tursunkulov, Deputy President, Veterinary Surveillance Committee, Ministry
of Agriculture, Astana:
Report date: 23 June 1999.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 10 June 1999.
Estimated date of first infection: 3 June 1999.
Outbreaks:
Location: Zhusaly colony, Karmakshin district, Kyzyl-Orda
region
No. of outbreaks: 4

Description of affected population: sedentary local breed cattle of either
sex, aged between 12 months and 12 years.
Total number of animals in the outbreaks:
species: bovine
susceptible: 235
cases: ---
deaths: 4
destroyed: 0
slaughtered: 0
Causal agent: virus type O.
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: investigations under way.
B. Mode of spread: contact with sick animals.
Control measures during reporting period: quarantine of affected farms;
treatment of affected animals; movement control inside the country and at
frontiers; vaccination.
--
ProMED
<promed@usa.healthnet.org>
[Note the outbreak was detected on 10 June 1999 & reported (nationally?) on
23 June 1999 but only notified internationally on 24 Sep 1999 - Mod.JW
.............................................tg/jw

